<!--HOW TO USE APP-->
<section class="two">
  <div class=" text-center mt-5 p-5">
    <div class="row">
      <div id="carouselExampleControls" class="carousel slide container" data-bs-ride="carousel">
        <div class="carousel-inner">
          <div class="carousel-item active">
            <p class="d-block w-100 pe-5 ps-5" >
              Open the app and click on the “Sign Up” button.
              Provide your email address, create a strong password, and complete any other required fields.
              Verify your email (usually by clicking a link sent to your inbox).

            </p>
          </div>

          
          <div class="carousel-item ">
            <p class="d-block w-100 ps-5 pe-5" >
              To select a which e
              Navigate to the “Emergency Contacts” section.
              Add the phone numbers of trusted friends, family members, or emergency services.
              These contacts will be notified in case of an emergency.
              On the home page you can find quick links to our the emergency service providers

            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="carousel-item ps-5 pe-5">
            <p class="d-block w-100" >
              In the app, find the “Nearby Police Stations” feature.
              Click on it to access a map or list view.
              The app will show nearby police stations based on your current location.
              You can also search for police stations in specific areas.</p>

            </p>
          </div>
          
          
        <div class="slider_buttons">
        <button class="carousel-control-prev" type="button" data-bs-target="#carouselExampleControls" data-bs-slide="prev">
          <span class="carousel-control-prev-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span class="visually-hidden">Previous</span>
        </button>
        <button class="carousel-control-next" type="button" data-bs-target="#carouselExampleControls" data-bs-slide="next">
          <span class="carousel-control-next-icon" aria-hidden="true" ></span>
          <span class="visually-hidden">Next</span>
        </button>
        </div> 
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>


</section >


   



